    29 Products Basically Everyone Could Benefit From Owning

    "Oh, yes. I need that." —me and who knows, maybe you

    by Kayla Suazo

    BuzzFeed Staff

    1. A pair of blue-light glasses to help you get through all those emails without getting a headache from blue light. They minimize ~digital eye strain~ to prevent midday crashes caused by your glaring screen, so you actually stay in the zone.

    2. Blue Apron — a meal subscription service that'll send ya everything you need (plus chef-designed recipes!) for some stress-feel dinners. Don't stress about going to the store, wasting food, or wondering what the heck to make, because this service does all the work for you.

    Advertisement

    3. A magnetic dry-erase board perfect for whatever weekly reminders you need to leave yourself before you start the day. DON'T FORGET TO WATER THE PLANTS!

    4. A 1-ounce bottle of dry shampoo POWDER (!!) that'll let ya ditch the shower on late mornings and rock hair that *looks* like it just got a fresh wash. Keep it in your purse for any midday touchups. Easy peasy.

    5. A memory foam seat cushion to save your butt and back from the wrath of desk chairs, uncomfortable car seats, and really anywhere you do a lot of sitting.

    Advertisement

    6. A set of colorful bento boxes so it's super easy to meal prep for the week and *not* stress each day on what to eat. A week of lunches doesn't seem so daunting now!

    7. A mini sewing kit with everything you need to fix a fashion emergency! Be prepared to handle snags, rips, loose buttons, and more with this in arm's reach.

    Advertisement

    8. A very nice mattress topper that'll get you on your way to better sleep. We might not be able to replace our mattress, but we can add a layer of heavenly, responsive memory foam to help our backs and our zzz's.

    9. A teeny migraine stick made with therapeutic essential oils that can relieve migraine pain and give you some dang peace during stressful weeks. Keep one handy so you're ready whenever a headache strikes.

    Advertisement

    10. A Tushy bidet that'll become one of those, how did I not buy this sooner? purchases. Save toilet paper and get a better clean with this magical device that even features adjustable pressure. Ahhh – a spa for the bum.

    11. A cookbook featuring recipes that can all be made in one pot, skillet, or slow cooker. Dinner and cleanup has never looked so promising.

    Advertisement

    12. A Tide To Go stick that'll have you prepared for whatever coffee, lunch, or wine spill comes your way throughout the day.

    13. Oil-blotting wipes to swipe away that shiny 3 p.m. forehead without disturbing your makeup.

    Advertisement

    14. A pack of stainless-steel straws with silicone tips (and a cleaning brush!) that'll make drinking out of them softer on your teeth. Reducing plastic is rad and now you can do it all 👏the👏 time👏.

    15. A set of cable clips that can be used to organize and prop up your chargers (because nothing is more annoying than your charger slipping behind your nightstand), *or* as a clever way to store your toothbrushes.

    Advertisement

    16. A coffee subscription service so you can try coffee from around the world right in the comfort of your own home. Now, a cup of this is something worth waking up early for!

    17. A universal socket that uses steel spring pins to adjust and fit a variety of screws, nuts, and bolts so the days of carrying 20+ different tools are O-V-E-R.

    Advertisement

    18. A suuuuuuuuuper sleek electric toothbrush made with charcoal-infused bristles, three brushing modes, and a battery with a four week lifespan so you don't have to worry about constantly recharging. Yeah, this is like the king of toothbrushes.

    19. Clarifying shampoo you can use once a week in place of your usual shampoo to remove that annoying residue left behind from heavy hair products.

    Advertisement

    20. Just a really good chef's knife. It's time guys. It's time to ditch the flimsy knives we've had since college, and splurge on at least one nice option that'll cut, slice, and dice like pure butter.

    21. A discreet little password book that'll serve ya a friendly reminder when you can't remember what your favorite pizza topping was in 2007.

    Advertisement

    22. Foot Cardigan — aka a sock club and the only club you will ever need to be a part of. They send you a fresh pair of stylish socks each month, not to mention a whole bunch of perks. Who doesn't *need*/*want* more socks? Nobody!

    23. A powerful mouthwash for quickly getting rid of morning breath. Whether or not you have time to brush your teeth is your business, I am just here to show you a great product that can help bad breath!

    Advertisement

    24. A Glossier exfoliating solution that gently scrubs away dead skin to help reduce the appearance of blemishes, redness, and pores so skin looks smoother.

    25. An automatic pan stirrer your arms will be forever thankful for when a recipe calls for continuous stirring.

    Advertisement

    26. An "Always Pan" — aka a pan that, spoiler alert, does it all so *you* don't have to do it all for dinner. It's made to replace eight pieces of cookware so you can saute, fry, boil, sear, literally do it all, with just one pan. Cleaning up one pan is my kinda love language.

    27. A strengthening cream that'll condition nails and cuticles with a calcium- and vitamin rich-formula to prevent splits, cracks, and breakage.

    Advertisement

    28. And an easy-to-clean tongue scraper that'll quite literally scrape away the funk and gunk your electric toothbrush and powerful mouthwash don't seem to put a dent into.

    29. A simple label maker that'll let you mark all your jars, bins, and files with total ease. Will you start labeling everything? Probably. And you should.

    Me to all of these things!!!!
